def smallest_index(nums):
    for i in range(len(nums)):
        if i % 10 == nums[i]:
            return i
    return -1
```

    We need to find the smallest index i such that i % 10 is equal to nums[i]. To achieve this, we simply iterate through the array using a for loop. For each index i, we calculate i % 10 and compare it with nums[i]. If i % 10 is equal to nums[i], we return the index i. If no such index exists, we return -1. All language implementations follow similar logic.

